      "name": "Vazgorlu",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Vazgorlu Digestion",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises pg. 83",
                "aonid": 15,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises pg. 83",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises",
              "page": 83,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "A vazgorlu gains nourishment from both the biological result of digesting a creature and the metaphysical consumption of that creature\u2019s connection to the multiverse once it has been cut off from other dimensions. As such, a vazgorlu can only be truly sated while consuming prey in its own lair, where it can devour a creature in both ways.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises pg. 83",
            "aonid": 15,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises pg. 83",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Pathfinder #150: Broken Promises",
          "page": 83,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "The arthropod monstrosity known as a vazgorlu makes its home on the Astral Plane or inside of a stable portal, ambushing creatures that travel there using dimensional magic.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
